e that remains for us?   Some leavings brought relief, even joy, while others brought pain and suffering. Whether the cause was infirmity, impending death, or simply exhaustion and ennui, the ways these influential voices fell silent offer poignant examples of people withdrawing from the world's stage. Throughout this learned and moving book, Taylor probes how the art of living involves learning to leave gracefully.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 22. Okt 2019) 7aRELIGION / Philosophy.2bisacsh40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300231427423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300231427.jpg  aGBV-deGruyter-alles